actually understand

00:23:21.570 --> 00:23:23.010
where she is relative to that.

00:23:23.010 --> 00:23:25.110
And it's not
commented on at all.

00:23:25.110 --> 00:23:27.924
I mean, it just exists
there, and so it's

00:23:27.924 --> 00:23:28.840
an interesting moment.

00:23:31.640 --> 00:23:34.680
AUDIENCE: So I realize
that you don't really

00:23:34.680 --> 00:23:38.970
have a chance to know
how far out the show is

00:23:38.970 --> 00:23:40.100
going to keep going.

00:23:40.100 --> 00:23:41.300
NAREN SHANKAR: Forever.

00:23:41.300 --> 00:23:42.800
AUDIENCE: Well,
that would be great,

00:23:42.800 --> 00:23:45.360
because I'm really enjoying it.

00:23:45.360 --> 00:23:47.790
But I'm curious.

00:23:47.790 --> 00:23:49.930
How do you structure
things in terms

00:23:49.930 --> 00:23:52.770
of like, this is
where we're at, this

00:23:52.770 --> 00:23:55.070
is where the books are
going, this is where we want

00:23:55.070 --> 00:23:58.720
to end the season, which may
or may not coincide directly

00:23:58.720 --> 00:24:02.530
with the end of the book, and
thinking like how far ahead do

00:24:02.530 --> 00:24:04.520
you think on that stuff?

00:24:04.520 --> 00:24:07.030
I know you've been picked
up for the second season,

00:24:07.030 --> 00:24:09.990
and the books, obviously,
are going on for a while,

00:24:09.990 --> 00:24:11.520
and there's more books planned.

00:24:11.520 --> 00:24:17.350
And so I'm really curious how
the structure of the TV seasons

00:24:17.350 --> 00:24:20.470
and the structure of the books
are combined in a show running

00:24:20.470 --> 00:24:21.329
sense.

00:24:21.329 --> 00:24:22.870
MARK FERGUS: I mean,
we're just going

00:24:22.870 --> 00:24:25.579
with our gut in terms
of each season needs

00:24:25.579 --> 00:24:30.230
to be a complete experience, a
complete story, like a 10 hour,

00:24:30.230 --> 00:24:34.844
13 hour movie with
its own structure.

00:24:34.844 --> 00:24:37.010
Then we fit that into a
larger structure of seasons.

00:24:37.010 --> 00:24:39.270
I think we're just
going toward what

00:24:39.270 --> 00:24:42.040
is the next big
evolution of the story.

00:24:42.040 --> 00:24:43.790
It doesn't always
coincide with the books,

00:24:43.790 --> 00:24:46.780
because we don't have
to it's crazy to go

00:24:46.780 --> 00:24:48.860
as fast as the books.

00:24:48.860 --> 00:24:51.490
To cram it in, we'd be losing
so much great material.

00:24:51.490 --> 00:24:56.116
So one of the things we had to
learn, Hawk and I, from Naren

00:24:56.116 --> 00:24:57.370
is slow down.

00:24:57.370 --> 00:24:58.730
Stop burning through the story.

00:24:58.730 --> 00:25:02.620
Stop trying to get to a fixed
point because the book did.

00:25:02.620 --> 00:25:05.530
And you're going to have to
blow past all this amazing stuff

00:25:05.530 --> 00:25:06.820
to get to a point.

00:25:06.820 --> 00:25:09.070
So I think we've
adjusted our pace

00:25:09.070 --> 00:25:11.957
to learn to tell the story,
bring the novellas in, bring

00:25:11.957 --> 00:25:12.540
characters in.

00:25:12.540 --> 00:25:14.400
Let the thing evolve
at its own pace,

00:25:14.400 --> 00:25:18.510
and each big chunk of
it, if we're lucky enough

00:25:18.510 --> 00:25:22.090
to keep going, will just
find the next great turning

00:25:22.090 --> 00:25:23.530
point and the next great--

00:25:23.530 --> 00:25:25.750
The first season, we
would have ideally loved

00:25:25.750 --> 00:25:27.190
to get through the first book.

00:25:27.190 --> 00:25:29.240
It wasn't feasible
for a lot of reasons,

00:25:29.240 --> 00:25:30.420
and not even advisable.

00:25:30.420 --> 00:25:34.090
So we picked a great
turning point of the book

00:25:34.090 --> 00:25:37.090
to be the season end,
and we could get there

00:25:37.090 --> 00:25:38.840
at a pace that was appropriate.

00:25:38.840 --> 00:25:40.500
So it's a hard
question to answer,

00:25:40.500 --> 00:25:43.650
but every block needs
to feel like-- I always

00:25:43.650 --> 00:25:48.024
think of it as to feel like its
own contained, awesome season.

00:25:48.024 --> 00:25:49.440
Whether or not you
get a next one,

00:25:49.440 --> 00:25:51.590
you end on a really
amazing point

00:25:51.590 --> 00:25:53.900
that feels like the
characters have evolved.

00:25:53.900 --> 00:25:55.760
The story has evolved.

00:25:55.760 --> 00:25:57.860
We've opened up the
universe that much more,

00:25:57.860 --> 00:26:00.690
and then hopefully, we'll be
back to fill in more stuff.

00:26:00.690 --> 00:26:02.610
NAREN SHANKAR: In both
season 1 and season 2,

00:26:02.610 --> 00:26:07.330
we started the year by a few
weeks of just discussion,

00:26:07.330 --> 00:26:10.991
really, about what that very
broad structure of the show

00:26:10.991 --> 00:26:11.490
was.

00:26:11.490 --> 00:26:13.110
And season one was 10 episode.

00:26:13.110 --> 00:26:15.520
Season 2 is going to be 13.

00:26:15.520 --> 00:26:20.570
You have these books that
have a really strong, well

00:26:20.570 --> 00:26:22.530
delineated plot framework.

00:26:22.530 --> 00:26:26.130
And so there's probably
several points in book one

00:26:26.130 --> 00:26:28.590
that we could have chosen
to end the season at.

00:26:28.590 --> 00:26:31.270
We picked one in particular,
and the same thing

00:26:31.270 --> 00:26:34.830
is happening as we're
going into book 2.

00:26:34.830 --> 00:26:37.620
But what you get is,
once you understand what

00:26:37.620 --> 00:26:40.270
the pace of the show is, once
you get a broad idea of where

00:26:40.270 --> 00:26:44.260
you want to go, it
starts to lay down,

00:26:44.260 --> 00:26:46.660
and you start to
see episodically

00:26:46.660 --> 00:26:48.040
what the events are.

00:26:48.040 --> 00:26:51.335
And yeah, we're very
tightly serialized,

00:26:51.335 --> 00:26:53.043
so you can watch the
whole thing through,

00:26:53.043 --> 00:26:54.740
and it's telling you a story.

00:26:54.740 --> 00:26:56.920
But if you watch the
individual episodes,

00:26:56.920 --> 00:27:00.910
there's usually some sense of
completeness, episodically.

00:27:00.910 --> 00:27:03.740
And so those first few
weeks of the season

00:27:03.740 --> 00:27:06.150
is where you really
talk that stuff through,

00:27:06.150 --> 00:27:11.730
and pretty quickly, you get
to an understanding of how

00:27:11.730 --> 00:27:14.650
the season wants
to lay itself down,

00:27:14.650 --> 00:27:17.220
and the story that
you want to tell.

00:27:17.220 --> 00:27:18.400
It's usually there.

00:27:18.400 --> 00:27:20.090
You just have to find it.

00:27:20.090 --> 00:27:25.850
And I think that when
we come into the season,

00:27:25.850 --> 00:27:28.190
somebody will say, well, hey,
what if we ended it here?

00:27:28.190 --> 00:27:29.610
And everybody's like, that's
a great place to end it,

00:27:29.610 --> 00:27:31.150
and just seems very natural.

00:27:31.150 --> 00:27:34.550
And so I think that's at
least our plan going forward

00:27:34.550 --> 00:27:35.712
to continue that.

00:27:35.712 --> 00:27:37.170
AUDIENCE: I thought
where you chose

00:27:37.170 --> 00:27:39.397
to end the first season
a good stopping point.

00:27:39.397 --> 00:27:40.230
NAREN SHANKAR: Nice.

